                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding>
                                <p>Contemporary binding from <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100205">Vadstena Monastery.</placeName> Brown leather over wooden boards. 4 double bands and endbands. 2 hook-clasps with long clasps and short leather straps. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, in brown ink: <quote>CC</quote>; in black ink: <quote>131</quote>; stamped in gold: <quote>A 32</quote>; brown ink on torn label: <quote>32</quote>.</p>
                                <p>Binding probably by <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102551">Niels Bookbinder</persName>, active in Vadstena at the end of the 15th century; see <bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107151">Collijn (1903)</title>
                                        <citedRange from="144" to="145" unit="page"/>
                                    </bibl>. Several examples of stamps used by Niels are found in Sten G. Lindberg’s archive, Kungliga Biblioteket, Band 10:4 Niels–band och andra gnidebilder, Acc. 2005/28.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="240" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="170" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="100" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <decoNote type="tooling">
                                    <p>Blind-tooling. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>: Double frame filled with stamps of fleur-de-lis and roses. Panel blind stamped with large lozenges filled with vegetative shapes. <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>: Multi-line frame. Diamond pattern panel filled with multiple stamps of fleur-de-lis and roses. <locus from="Head" to="Head" scheme="other"/>, <locus from="Tail" to="Tail" scheme="other"/>, and <locus from="Fore-edge" to="Fore-edge" scheme="other"/>: Blind-tooling also found on the edges of the cover.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <condition>Covers torn and cracked in places. Endbands and one of the raised bands exposed.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
