                                <title type="uniform">Revelations, Book 5</title>
                                <rubric>prologus libri questionum qui est quintus liber celestium revelacionum beate Birgitte</rubric>
                                <incipit>Incipit Quintus liber celestium revelacionum Christi ad beatam Birgittam de regno Swecie</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="false">Ergo qui ad ista loca uenerit mundus cum bona et perfecta uoluntate habebit uidere et gustare quam dulcis et suauis sum ego deus Itaque cum ueneris ad ista loca ostendam tibi plura et cetera</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Explicit quintus liber questionum </finalRubric>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107147">Bergh (1971)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="97" to="175" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="31v" to="144v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100481"> Birgitta Birgersdotter </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="uniform">Revelations, Book 6</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit sextus liber revelacionum celestium beate Birgitte de regno Swecie rubrica primi capituli. Verba matris dei ad sponsam narrancia pulchritudinem Christi et qualiter frequenter iudei in aliquo agone cordis positi ibant ad inspiciendum vultum eius et consolabantur Capitulum primum </rubric>
                                <incipit>Mater dei loquabatur ad sponsam dicens Ego sum regina celi </incipit>
                                <explicit defective="true">Alioquin labor suus superuacuus et oracio sua erunt ei minus in coronam</explicit>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107148">Bergh (1991)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="59" to="270" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="144v" to="191v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100481"> Birgitta Birgersdotter </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="uniform">Revelations, Book 7</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit septimus liber celestium Reuelacionum Beate Birgitte de regno Swecie Rubrica primi capituli. Reuelacio quam habuit domina Brigitta in Roma post annum Iubilei in qua uirgo Maria pronunciat ei que itura esset in iherusalem et bethleem quando placuerit deo promittens ei tunc ostendere sibi modum quomodo ipsa peperit filium suum benedictum </rubric>
                                <incipit>Cum esset in Roma Beata birgitta sponsa christi et quadam uice oracioni </incipit>
                                <explicit defective="false">Dicta uero missa et sacramentis perceptis cum maxima deuocione et reuerencia inter manus predictarum personarum emisit spiritum</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Explicit septimus liber celestis reuelacionum christi ad sponsam beatam Birgittam</finalRubric>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107149">Bergh (1967)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="113" to="215" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="191v" to="211v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName>Alfonso Pecha</persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="uniform">Epistola solitarii ad reges</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit epistola solitarii ad Reges. <sic>Reprehendit</sic> hic illi qui ex abrupto et improuiso nullo examine precedente approbant aut reprobant personas se asserentes habere uisiones et reuelationes diuinas </rubric>
                                <incipit>O Serenissimi Reges vtinam veri reges in christo </incipit>
                                <explicit defective="false">ut ex omnibus supradictis patet breuiter ex dictis omnium doctorum et sanctorum patrum super hac materia multipharie diffuse loquencium</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Explicit prologus domini Alphonsi </finalRubric>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107150">Hans Aili (2002)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="48" to="81" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="211v" to="212v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100481"> Birgitta Birgersdotter </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="uniform">Prologue to Book 8</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit prologus libri celestis imperatoris ad reges in quo continetur modus compilacionis eius Et admonentur reges et principes quod recipiant hunc librum deuote et humiliter de manu dei et cum corde et opere sequantur hanc doctrinam frequenter. Capitulum viii </rubric>
                                <incipit>Ad presentis quippe libri nunc iam materiam descendendo Sciendum est quod iste liber infrascriptus intitulatur Celestis imperatoris ad reges</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="false">Qui rex est regum ac dominus dominancium in secula seculorum Amen</explicit>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107150">Hans Aili (2002)</title>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="212v" to="293r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100481"> Birgitta Birgersdotter </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="uniform">Revelations, Book 8</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit octauus liber celestis Imperatoris ad reges reuelacionum diuinitus Beate brigitte de regno Swecie Rubrika primi capituli. / Summus imperator Christi per sponsam loquitur ad reges ostendens se esse uerum omnium creatorem et regem in trinitate et vnitate regnantem Et dicit qualiter mundum ordinauit regendum duplici potestate scilicet ecclesiastica et laycali <sic>qui</sic> in apostolis petro et paulo principaliter designantur Capitulum primum</rubric>
                                <incipit>Vidi pallacium grande incomprehensibile magnitudine simile celo sereno</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="false">Excutite graue iugum dyaboli a uobis et recordemini caritatis mee et uidebitis in consciencia uestra quod ego sum suauis et mitis</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Explicit liber octauus celestis imperatoris ad reges et cetera</finalRubric>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="293v" to="293v" scheme="folios"/>: blank </note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107150">Hans Aili (2002)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="84" to="224" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
